INTRODUCTION: Use vxperf2 to analyze, summarize and visualize any text
databases. (e.g. Logs generated by any OS monitoring tool.)
REQUIRED: Perl, Gnuplot
INSTALLATION: perl install.pl
DOCUMENTATION: perldoc vxperf2, perldoc log2db
BUILD: perl build.pl
REFERENCES: http://bsravanin.blogspot.com/search/label/vxperf2
LICENSE: MIT License
COURTESY: SYMANTEC CORPORATION

I attempted this to meet most of my day-to-day analysis requirements, and also
as an exercise to learn Perl. Before I knew about R. I no longer maintain it,
but still find uses of it.
